---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms & Conditions — Corney's Automotive Services" description="Terms and Conditions for Corney's Automotive Services, Taree NSW.">
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: April 2026</p>

      <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-8">

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">1. About these terms</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">These Terms and Conditions apply to all services provided by Corney's Automotive Services (ABN 72 659 468 550), located at 16 Albert Lane, Taree NSW 2430. By booking a service, requesting a quote, or bringing your vehicle to our workshop, you agree to these terms.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">2. Quotes and pricing</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>Quotes provided online, by phone, or in person are estimates only. Final pricing may vary based on the actual condition of the vehicle, complexity of the work, or parts required once the vehicle is inspected.</li>
            <li>We will always contact you before proceeding with any work that would result in a charge significantly above the quoted amount.</li>
            <li>Our standard labour rate is $130 per hour + GST. This may vary for specialist work.</li>
            <li>All prices displayed on our website are indicative and include GST unless otherwise stated.</li>
            <li>Fixed-price services (such as AC regas) are charged at the stated price for standard passenger vehicles. Non-standard vehicles may attract a different rate — we will advise you before proceeding.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">3. Bookings</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>Bookings made through our website are requests only and are not confirmed until you receive confirmation from us by phone or email.</li>
            <li>We reserve the right to reschedule bookings in exceptional circumstances. We will give you as much notice as possible and work to find a suitable alternative time.</li>
            <li>If you need to cancel or reschedule, please contact us as soon as possible so we can offer the slot to another customer.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">4. Authorisation to proceed</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>By leaving your vehicle with us, you authorise us to inspect it and to carry out the work we have discussed or quoted.</li>
            <li>We will contact you before performing any work beyond the original scope of the booking if it will result in additional costs.</li>
            <li>If we are unable to contact you after reasonable attempts and the vehicle needs to be moved or made safe, we reserve the right to take reasonable action.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">5. Parts and materials</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>We use quality parts that meet or exceed manufacturer specifications. We may use genuine, OEM-equivalent, or aftermarket parts as appropriate and will advise you of options where relevant.</li>
            <li>If you supply your own parts, we will fit them but cannot warranty the parts themselves — only our labour. We may decline to fit supplied parts if we consider them unsuitable or unsafe.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">6. Warranty on our work</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>Our workmanship is covered by a reasonable warranty in accordance with Australian Consumer Law. If you experience an issue with work we have performed, contact us promptly and we will assess it.</li>
            <li>Warranty does not cover issues caused by subsequent damage, misuse, or failure of unrelated components.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">7. Payment</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>Payment is due upon completion of work unless otherwise agreed in advance.</li>
            <li>We accept cash, EFTPOS, and bank transfer. Credit card surcharges may apply.</li>
            <li>We reserve the right to retain your vehicle until payment is received in full.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">8. Liability</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>We take care of every vehicle entrusted to us. However, we are not liable for any pre-existing faults or damage that were not caused by our work.</li>
            <li>We are not responsible for personal belongings left in the vehicle.</li>
            <li>Our liability for any claim is limited to the value of the work performed.</li>
            <li>Nothing in these terms limits your rights under the Australian Consumer Law.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">9. Safety inspections (Pink Slips &amp; Blue Slips)</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>Safety inspections are conducted in accordance with NSW Transport for NSW requirements. Our assessments are independent and based on the condition of the vehicle at the time of inspection.</li>
            <li>If your vehicle does not pass, we will explain what needs to be rectified. Repairs are quoted and performed separately — the inspection fee is charged regardless of the outcome.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">10. Accuracy of information</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
            <li>You agree to provide accurate information about your vehicle and the issues you are experiencing. Inaccurate information may affect our ability to diagnose or quote correctly.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">11. Governing law</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">These terms are governed by the laws of New South Wales, Australia. Any disputes will be subject to the jurisdiction of NSW courts.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">12. Contact us</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">If you have any questions about these Terms and Conditions, please contact us:</p>
          <div class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
            <p><strong>Corney's Automotive Services</strong></p>
            <p>16 Albert Lane, Taree NSW 2430</p>
            <p>Phone: <a href="tel:0265526131" class="text-red-600 hover:underline">(02) 6552 6131</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
